<text>An eastern seaboard can mean any easternmost part of a continent, or its countries, states and cities.

Eastern seaboard may also refer to:

* Eastern states of Australia
* East Coast of the United States
* Eastern seaboard of Thailand
* Northeast megalopolis, often coterminous with &quot;Eastern seaboard&quot;, the most heavily urbanized region of the United States

